{{Expand Japanese|topic=bio|春日娘子|date=January 2023}}
{{Infobox royalty |consort = yes |name = Kasuga no Iratsume |succession = [[Empress of Japan|Empress consort of Japan]] |reign = 499–507 |spouse = [[Emperor Buretsu]] |issue = |royal house = [[Imperial House of Japan]] |father = |mother = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |date of burial = |place of burial = |}}
'''Kasuga no Iratsume''' (? – fl. 507) was [[Empress of Japan]] as the consort of [[Emperor Buretsu]].<ref> Anston, W.G. (1896). Transactions and Proceedings of The Japan Society, London. Supplement I. Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697. Vol. 1. London: Kegan Paul, Trench, Trüber, & Co.</ref>
She is the only Japanese empress consort whose parents are unknown.
